\\par
1. 30-Second Intro\\par
Bus Management System is a full-stack web app for managing buses, drivers, routes, student allocations, attendance, and entry-exit logs with role-based access. It uses React frontend and Node.js/Express backend with MySQL.\\par
\\par
2. Problem Statement\\par
- Manual transport operations are slow and error-prone.\\par
- No centralized visibility for admin/transport/staff/driver/student.\\par
- Attendance and trip logs are difficult to audit.\\par
\\par
3. Objectives\\par
- Centralized transport operations dashboard.\\par
- Role-specific workflows.\\par
- Secure login + authorization.\\par
- Attendance and audit traceability.\\par
- Scalable API-driven architecture.\\par
\\par
4. Tech Stack\\par
- Frontend: React\\par
- Backend: Node.js, Express\\par
- Database: MySQL (Sequelize ORM)\\par
- Auth: JWT (access + refresh)\\par
- Validation: Joi\\par
- API Docs: Swagger\\par
- Testing: Jest + Supertest\\par
- Deployment support: Docker + GitHub\\par
\\par
5. Roles & Features\\par
- Admin: manage users, buses, routes, drivers, audit logs.\\par
- Transport Incharge: operational oversight.\\par
- Staff: student attendance + allocations.\\par
- Driver: driver attendance + entry/exit logs.\\par
- Student: view assigned bus/route details.\\par
\\par
6. Architecture\\par
- Routes -> Controllers -> Models -> MySQL\\par
- Middleware handles authentication, role checks (RBAC), validation, error handling, and audit logging.\\par
\\par
7. Demo Flow\\par
1. Login as Admin.\\par
2. Create Bus + Driver + Route.\\par
3. Login as Staff, assign/mark student attendance.\\par
4. Login as Driver, submit entry-exit log.\\par
5. Show audit logs as Admin.\\par
6. Show student view (read-only relevant data).\\par
\\par
8. Security/Quality Points\\par
- JWT auth and protected APIs.\\par
- Input validation with Joi.\\par
- Centralized error handling.\\par
- Audit logging for sensitive operations.\\par
- Integration tests for core API flows.\\par
\\par
9. Challenges Solved\\par
- Standardized backend on MySQL with Sequelize (single database stack).\\par
- Updated models/controllers/tests for Sequelize.\\par
- Cleaned repo hygiene (node_modules, .env not tracked).\\par
- Stabilized test cleanup and passing test suites.\\par
\\par
10. Future Enhancements\\par
- Live GPS tracking integration.\\par
- SMS/notification alerts.\\par
- Analytics dashboard (occupancy, punctuality).\\par
- Sequelize migrations for production-grade DB lifecycle.\\par
- Cloud deployment with monitoring.\\par
\\par
Likely HOD Questions + Answers\\par
Q: Why MySQL?\\par
A: Structured relational data, strong consistency, and better fit for linked entities like users, routes, buses, and logs.\\par
\\par
Q: How is security handled?\\par
A: JWT auth, RBAC middleware, Joi validation, and audit trails.\\par
\\par
Q: Is it scalable?\\par
A: Modular backend, API-first design, Dockerized deployment path, and clear separation of concerns.\\par
\\par
Q: How do you ensure reliability?\\par
A: Automated integration tests and standardized error handling.\\par
